Deep Potato - the hyperspectral imagery of potato leaves with reference agronomic measurements dataset: towards potato physiological features modelling¶

Authors:¶

  • Ruszczak Bogdan 1 QZ Solutions Sp. z o.o., Opole, Poland 2 Department of Electrical, Control and Computer Engineering, Opole University of Technology, Opole, Poland

  • Dominika Boguszewska-Mańkowska

    • Plant Breeding and Acclimatization Institute - National Research Institute Jadwisin, Poland
  • link to the repository https://data.mendeley.com/datasets/xn2wy75f8m
  • to cite this database please refer to the paper:
    • B. Ruszczak, D. Boguszewska-Mańkowska: Deep Potato - the hyperspectral imagery of potato leaves with reference agronomic measurements dataset: towards potato physiological features modelling, Data in Brief, vol. , https://doi.org/**/ (to be updated)

Description¶

  • the dataset contains 8 high resolution, 150 band, hyperspectral orthophotomaps for deep learning modelling
    • 8 full resolution orthophotomaps (ENVI format - 8 .hdr and .bsq files),
    • 80 extracted, masked hyperspectral images (numpy array format - 80 .npz files),
  • for a reference, there are two table supplemented, with 60 laboratory examination results and 74 physiological measurements, based on collected plants' material (2 .geojson files).
